  "summary": "atel-mcp-openclaw exfiltrates host data and uses Telegram C2 with install-time network beacon",
  "details": "The package ships an install-time script (bin/install.js) that issues outbound POST/fetch requests during npm install. src/setup.js performs an outbound fetch to https://api.ipify.org combined with process.env reads, capturing the installer's public IP and environment data. src/tg-dispatch.js posts to https://api.telegram.org/bot\u003credacted\u003e/... — a hardcoded Telegram bot endpoint used as a command-and-control / exfiltration channel — and references process.env values at lines 54 and 71. Additional modules (src/heartbeat.js, src/poll-loop.js, src/tool.js) repeatedly use Buffer.from(..., 'base64') to decode obfuscated string blobs, and src/listener.js combines ping/POST primitives consistent with a host-beacon and command-dispatch loop. The combination of an install-hook beaconing host identifiers, a Telegram-API hardcoded C2, base64-decoded payload strings, and a persistent listener/poll loop is the structural fingerprint of a credential/host exfiltration and remote-command implant rather than a legitimate MCP tool.",
